snippet.title: Multiplying Binomials: The Distributive Property and FOIL Method [fbt]
snippet.description:
This multiply binomials video by Fort Bend Tutoring shows the process of multiplying binomials using the distributive property and the FOIL method. This math concept, multiplying binomials using foil, is used in all algebra, geometry, precalculus, trigonometry and calculus courses. Eight (8) binomial examples are shown in detail. Intro/Outro done by Chuck Knipp's Shirley Q. Liquor. Instruction of foil method algebra by Larry "Mr. Whitt" Whittington. Multiplying polynomials distributive property (fort bend tutoring multiplying binomials) [multiplying binomial]

[fbt] Timestamps
02:15 [1] (x - 3)(x + 5)
04:21 [2] (2x - 7)(8x + 1)
05:34 [3] (x - 5)(14x - 3)
06:47 [4] (4a - 3)(4a + 3)
08:23 [5] (2m - 3)²
10:25 [6] (4x + 9y)²
12:01 [7] (3x - y)(2x + 5y)
13:14 [8] (5x²y + 3z)(11x - z)
